{"TopicId":126779,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Speaking Kerbalese","CreatedByName":"KAL 9000","CreatedById":140704,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T15:17:51Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KAL 9000","CreatedById":140704,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T15:17:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know it\u0027s backwards Spanish, but how on Kerbin could the Kerbals develop this with no contact with Earth/Mexico/Spain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-01T15:25:01Z\u0022 title=\u002212/01/2015 03:25  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 1, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by KAL 9000\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gaarst","CreatedById":126740,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T15:36:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReversing recorded samples from the devteam was easier than inventing a whole new language.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might also wonder why \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.google.co.uk/webhp?hl=en#hl=en-GB\u0026amp;q=a\u002Blong\u002Btime\u002Bago\u002Bin\u002Ba\u002Bgalaxy\u002Bfar\u002Bfar\u002Baway\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ea long time ago, in a galaxy far far away\u003C/a\u003E, everyone spoke english besides some alien races (oh, and there were humans too).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T15:50:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know about you, but that continent the KSC is on kind of looks like South America. And since Kerbin is an analog to Earth, it makes sense they would develop a similar language.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nacir\u00E9maduS?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"worir4","CreatedById":75980,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T15:53:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe devs are actually kerbals. They brought kerbal language to Earth long ago.\u00A0Early Spanish people adapted Kerbal language into what is now known as Spanish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T15:58:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmaybe reversed Spanish is an optimal, either local or global in the calculus sense,\u00A0language and gradually all space faring races converge towards it. given the nature of kerbals i\u0027m not too surprised that they optimized language before ... other things.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Venusgate","CreatedById":125730,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-01T19:40:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222302964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221448985030\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258517\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022spink00\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, spink00 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know about you, but that continent the KSC is on kind of looks like South America. And since Kerbin is an analog to Earth, it makes sense they would develop a similar language.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nacir\u00E9maduS?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfrica...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T09:52:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222303409\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221448998840\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125730\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Venusgate\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Venusgate said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfrica...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nShh, it\u0027s a secret.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNot many knows, or rather accepts, that the spacefaring Kerbals came from planet Acirfa.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T12:22:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222302964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221448985030\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258517\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022spink00\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, spink00 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know about you, but that continent the KSC is on kind of looks like South America. And since Kerbin is an analog to Earth, it makes sense they would develop a similar language.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept that the language of South America was brought by Spanish invaders. KSC looks nothing like Spain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T12:28:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222302964\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221448985030\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258517\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022spink00\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 hours ago, spink00 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know about you, but that continent the KSC is on kind of looks like South America. And since Kerbin is an analog to Earth, it makes sense they would develop a similar language.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nacir\u00E9maduS?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but the spanish language was \u0022developed\u0022 in Spain. Just saying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\noops, sorry severedsolo, did not see your reply\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-02T12:28:51Z\u0022 title=\u002212/02/2015 12:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 2, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Dafni\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-02T13:25:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222304498\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221449059282\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dafni\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n54 minutes ago, Dafni said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but the spanish language was \u0022developed\u0022 in Spain. Just saying.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222304494\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221449058962\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002280345\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022severedsolo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, severedsolo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExcept that the language of South America was brought by Spanish invaders. KSC looks nothing like Spain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou guys are arguing with a man who thinks that languages are developed based on the shape of a continent. Be careful.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GoSlash27","CreatedById":111526,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-03T11:20:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbalese is not reversed Spanish. Spanish is reversed Kerbalese!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd FWIW, Spanish, like most Western languages, is really just a local dialect of Latin. The KSC home continent looks nothing like Italy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBest,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-Slashy\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-03T11:28:21Z\u0022 title=\u002212/03/2015 11:28  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 3, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by GoSlash27\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steuben","CreatedById":77368,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-03T11:56:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222305995\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221449141614\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022111526\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GoSlash27\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, GoSlash27 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd FWIW, Spanish, like most Western languages, is really just a local dialect of Latin. The KSC home continent looks nothing like Italy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmore like\u00A0a third. teutonic and what ever the parent of Russian is balance the rest.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-03T17:40:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222302929\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221448983071\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022140704\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022KAL 9000\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/1/2015, 4:17:51, KAL 9000 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know it\u0027s backwards Spanish, but how on Kerbin could the Kerbals develop this with no contact with Earth/Mexico/Spain?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLikely it\u0027s the other way around. Kerbals have been visiting Earth for centuries now. Maybe millennia. Who but Kerbals would even consider routinely flying aerodynamically and graviationally unfeasible designs that defy all known laws of physics (a.k.a. just about every U.F.O. ever \u0027sighted\u0027)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-03T21:19:10Z\u0022 title=\u002212/03/2015 09:19  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 3, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by swjr-swis\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ebecause spellspasm\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Foxster","CreatedById":113764,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-03T20:32:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe same kind of dinosaur fossils are found in southern Spain and Mexico, explained by continental drift (or\u00A0pre-historic space flight). Here is one discovered recently:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kerbal_skeleton_by_mchayoo-d6qr6u2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://orig04.deviantart.net/740f/f/2013/289/0/8/kerbal_skeleton_by_mchayoo-d6qr6u2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-12-03T20:42:38Z\u0022 title=\u002212/03/2015 08:42  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 3, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Foxster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jovus","CreatedById":117163,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-03T20:56:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually, it\u0027s a translation. Real \u0027Kerbali\u0027 sounds nothing like what \u003Cem\u003Ewe\u003C/em\u003E hear the Kerbals say, and the translator chose backward Spanish to preserve the \u0027feel\u0027 and \u0027sense\u0027 of their utterances.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022But,\u0022 you say, \u0022that doesn\u0027t make sense! Translations should be sensible, not gobbledegook!\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. Translations should reflect the source material. And here we have the secret of KSC: the Kerbals are all just screwing with each other by using their own form of an obtuse Pig Latin whose only real use is telling jokes, insults, and confusing the listener.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat Kerbals who \u003Cem\u003Earen\u0027t\u003C/em\u003E doing this sound like, nobody knows. First you\u0027d have to find one not affiliated with the Kerbal Space Program. Rumour has it there\u0027s a settlement at the deepest point of Kerbin\u0027s ocean...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"arsenal3185","CreatedById":154240,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-12-04T03:44:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222302967\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022126779\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221448985200\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275980\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022worir4\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/1/2015, 9:53:20, worir4 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe devs are actually kerbals. They brought kerbal language to Earth long ago.\u00A0Early Spanish people adapted Kerbal language into what is now known as Spanish.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNext time on\u00A0\u003Cem\u003EAncient Aliens\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}